CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1955, p. 27, reads: "Symphony Performers - This group of talented high school students were among those winning chairs in auditions for the Junior Symphony which will sit chair - for - chair with the Pittsburgh Symphony in the annual joint concert at Syria Mosque, which, this year will be held Feb. 2. Left to right, front row: Arlene Jackson and Patricia Prattis, both of Westinghouse High Schools, violins; center, left to right: Natalie Crowder and Helen and Gail Stroud, all of Westinghouse, violas, and Lawrence Keys of Oliver, string bass, and back row, left to right: Karl Porter, Westinghouse, bassoon; Andrew Hughey, Schenley, viola, and Samuel Person, Oliver, viola. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Junior Symphony members, front row from left: Arlene Jackson, Patricia Prattis (Jennings); center row: Natalie Crowder, Helen Stroud, Gail Stroud, Lawrence Keys; and rear: Karl Porter, Andrew Hughey, Samuel Person, posed on stairs, horizontal format
